\begin{align}
\lim_{n \to \infty}\bracks{{1 \over 2^{n}}\sum_{k = 1}^{n}
{{n \choose k} \over \root{k}}} & =
\lim_{n \to \infty}\bracks{{1 \over 2^{n}}\sum_{k = 1}^{n}
{n \choose k}\,{1 \over \root{\pi}}\int_{0}^{\infty}t^{-1/2}\expo{-kt}\,\dd t}
\\[5mm] & =
{1 \over \root{\pi}}\lim_{n \to \infty}\bracks{{1 \over 2^{n}}\int_{0}^{\infty}{\pars{1 + \expo{-t}}^{n} - 1 \over t^{1/2}}\,\dd t}
\\[5mm] & =
{1 \over \root{\pi}}\lim_{n \to \infty}\braces{{1 \over 2^{n - 1}}
\int_{0}^{\infty}\bracks{{\pars{1 + \expo{-t^{2}}}^{n} - 1}}\,\dd t}
\label{1}\tag{1}
\\[5mm] & =
{1 \over \root{\pi}}\lim_{n \to \infty}\bracks{{1 \over 2^{n - 1}}
\int_{0}^{\infty}\pars{2^{n} - 1}
\exp\pars{-\,{2^{n - 1} \over 2^{n} - 1}\,n\,t^{2}}\,\dd t}
\label{2}\tag{2}
\\[5mm] & = \bbx{\ds{0}}
\end{align}
In line \eqref{1}, I used the Laplace Method to 'arrive' to line \eqref{2}.

